the transformation of the political scene. The wave of establishment parties losing the voters’ support and unable to deal with many national and European level problems that faced the country. This led to the rise of strong oppositional anti-establishment party, ANO 2011 who has the biggest victory in any election throughout the Czech history. Similar to the Czech Pirate Party and five other anti-establishment parties, ANO 2011 also faced many problems due to its growing and developing process. However, sometime similar to Pirate Party, the voters in most area of the country still preferred ANO 2011 a lot more than other parties in the national elections. Even in the local elections, ANO didn’t out of the scene, which can explain the preference. This paper will come up with the most plausible explanation for these miracle.

An unrealistic situation

Results of local and national elections in Czech Republic has shown an unbelievable situation. Even though ANO is a political party in its very early formation stage, it still attracted the most voters of all parties. In the national election in 2017(1), ANO gathered 29.6% of the overall vote which constitute 94% of the seats in the house. In the regional elections the year before in 2016, ANO secured 35.1% of the vote which gives them around only 34% of the seats.
